description: Alabama head coach Nate Oats hasn't disciplined freshman standout Brandon Miller despite authorities saying Miller was involved to a degree in a murder near campus.

title: Ivanka Trump, Jared Kushner subpoenaed in Jan. 6 probe: report
description: Special counsel Jack Smith has subpoenaed former President Trump's daughter Ivanka Trump and his son-in-law Jared Kushner in his probe into the Jan. 6, 2021 Capitol riots.

title: Ethnic studies professor claims rejecting the term Latinx is 'transphobic': 'Perpetuates violence'
description: San Francisco Chronicle publishes an opinion piece criticizing those who reject the use of the term "LatinX" as being "transphobic" and perpetrating violence against trans people.

title: Former Trump donor explains why he's backing possible DeSantis White House run
description: Don Tapia, a former ambassador who served under the Trump administration, discussed why he would back Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis for the 2024 Republican nomination on "Your World with Neil Cavuto."

title: Suspected Haitian gang member tied to murders of 6 cops arrested
description: A suspected Haitian gang member who may be connected to the killings of six police officers was arrested in the Dominican Republic on Wednesday.

title: Michigan State's Tom Izzo calls for unity against gun violence after rivals show support following shooting
description: Archrivals Michigan and Michigan State were able to set aside their differences for a bit following the shooting on the campus in Lansing.

title: JESSE WATTERS: Is it too little, too late for Mayor Pete?
description: Fox News host Jesse Watters reacts to former President Trump's visit to East Palestine, Ohio and shreds Pete Buttigieg's response on "Jesse Watters Primetime."

title: Sen. John Kennedy: US 'can't blink' on support for Ukraine now
description: Sen. John Kennedy, R-La., joins "Your World" to discuss how America's support for Ukraine has impacted its relationships with China and Russia.

title: One Michigan State University shooting victim still in critical condition, four others stable
description: Michigan State University police said Wednesday that only one of the five students wounded in the campus shooting on Feb. 13 was still in critical condition.

title: Texas man gets 3 years for Capitol riot, AOC threats
description: Garret Miller of Texas has been sentenced to three years in prison for his role in the Jan. 6, 2021, Capitol riot, as well as threats issued to members of Congress.

title: Connecticut to pay $12M settlement in child neglect case
description: The state of Connecticut is set to pay a $12 million settlement in a child neglect case involving an infant placed with an abusive relative by the state in 2015.

title: Ohio looks to standardize election data statewide
description: Republican Ohio Secretary of State Frank LaRose introduced a plan to standardize and streamline collection of election data at the state level.

title: Virginia Dems rejects new communism curriculum after teachers union said it could offend Asians
description: Virginia Democrats rejected a bill that would have required teaching about the history of communism after a teachers union opposed it because it risked encouraging anti-Asian sentiment.

title: Smithsonian Air and Space Museum responds to House Republicans demanding answers for booting pro-life students
description: The Smithsonian Air and Space Museum responded to House Republican's demands for answers following the expulsion of a group of students for wearing pro-life hats.

title: Vermont weighs ending religious exemption for child abuse reporting laws
description: The Vermont Legislature is considering the removal of legal exemptions from child abuse and neglect reporting that clergymen and other religious leaders are currently granted.

title: Ex-Lakers guard Patrick Beverley trolls former team, wants to 'knock them out the playoffs'
description: Patrick Beverley was traded to the Orlando Magic just before the trade deadline, where he soon secured contract buyout with the team. He went on to sign with the Bulls.

title: Dick Van Dyke, 97, says ‘having a beautiful young wife half my age’ keeps him young
description: Dick Van Dyke says his "young" 51-year-old wife Arlene Silver is part of the reason he's remained so youthful at 97, along with good genes and exercise.

title: New York woman gets 4 1/2 years for role in Sarah Lawrence sex trafficking scheme
description: Isabella Pollok of New York was sentenced to over four years in prison for aiding in the extortion and abuse of victims of Larry Ray's decade-long sex trafficking scheme.

title: Female fashion designer alleges Sam Brinton wore her clothing that disappeared from airport in 2018
description: A female fashion designer based in Houston alleged that clothing worn by former DOE official Sam Brinton had been contained in her luggage that she reported missing in 2018.
